name: Basil & Bunny
directions: Walking into the restaurant, the bathroom is in a hallway towards the back right wall. Directly after walking through the doorway at the back right wall, turn left and the single stall bathroom door is immediately there.
comment: Very clean. There are grab bars.

name: JC Penney Avenues Mall
directions: Back of second floor between lingerie and mattresses
comment: Gendered single stall handicap rooms, and multi-stall gendered options.

name: The Abbey Restaurant
directions: Very back of the restaurant by the kitchen.
comment: Overall clean and in good shape

name: Little Louies
directions: Go inside and turn left.  2 gender neutral bathrooms.

name: Lakewood Public Library - Madison Branch
directions: Two single private restrooms on first floor. Family restroom with changing table in basement.
comment: Open to all

name: St. Paul Lutheran Church
comment: One gender-neutral single stall bathroom, plus gendered bathrooms that are safe to use according to gender identity. Affirming congregation.

name: 12/30 Club Honky Tonk Restaurant
comment: Go in and have a drink at the bar if you don't want to eat. The restrooms are in the back - a bunch of single stalls.

name: Family restroom
directions: Outside of stingray exhibit

name: Browne's
comment: Back of a café - you probably have to pay

name: Real Food Cafe
directions: Straight back from the front door
comment: 2 unisex single-user restrooms

name: Artists Emporium
directions: Back of the store, then turn right.(there is a sign indicating where the washrooms are/or u can ask an employee)

name: Mellow Mushroom
directions: When facing the Alice in Wonderland inspired mural, there will be a restroom inlaid into the wall directly to its left.
comment: I would assume, like at most sit-down restaurants, you would have to eat here for restroom access. I didn't mark it as accessible as I can't make that call. It has a fairly wide door and grab bars, but it doesn't have a lot of clearance inside to turn around.

name: Nouvelle Brewing by Travail
directions: If facing the counter to the right at the back of the building
comment: The bathroom is a shared sink space with like 6 stalls/rooms with full floor to ceiling doors connecting to it

name: Lowe’s
directions: To the right of the men’s and women’s bathrooms, to the left of the Employees breakroom
comment: Doors a bit tricky, push the top half a bit and It should close with force

name: JoRetro
directions: In the second smaller room in the left where the clothes are, go down the steps into that room and it’s right on the left.

name: Live Oak Park
directions: In the middle of the park by the playground
comment: You have to pay a three dollar park entrance fee but most of the time no one is manning the booths. The bathrooms are free and are normally always open as there are two all gender stalls

name: Gordon food service
directions: At the front of the store.
comment: Two bathrooms marked as gener neutral for anyone to use.

name: The Paperback Exchange Bookstore
directions: Back righthand corner of bookshop
comment: No purchase necessary to use the restroom. It's accessible but the isles are narrow

name: The Center
comment:
LGBTQ+ Center
safe place

name: Lightridge High School
directions: Between the band and choir room.
comment: You must be a student/employee or a visitor for a school event as far as I know.

name: Vegan Junk Food Bar
directions: Upstairs.

name: Red Lobster
directions: Gender neutral family restroom by front door

name: Cabela’s
directions: As soon as you enter turn right and you will find the washrooms.
comment: There is one unisex single stall washroom.

name: Starbucks
street: North Terminal Avenue Terminal Shopping Centre, 1150
comment: There are two single stall accessible gender neutral washrooms.

name: Serious Coffee Vancouver Island Conference Centre
comment: You have to be a paying customer. There and two single stall gender neutral bathrooms.

name: Dillards
directions: Walk to the near back left corner of the store. Go to Gift Wrap. Turn left. Walk forward. Turn right go forward, walk forward. Turn left where the sign says "Restroom". On top sign it is the male and female stick figure

name: newk's
directions: from the front door, head all the way to the back right of the restaurant. there are two (gendered) single occupancy bathrooms with changing tables & a lock.

name: Cefco Travel Plaza
directions: This is a small truck stop. There is one restroom near the diesel entrance labeled as "All Gender"

name: Cefco Travel Plaza
directions: At the rear of the store. This is a small truck stop and there is a restroom labeled "All Gender" at the diesel entrance

name: Costco
directions: Family single restroom

name: Target
directions: Have to ask for key at customer service for family restroom. In the front north entrance.

name: DoubleTree by Hilton Hotel Orlando at SeaWorld
directions: Main lobby, just past check-in desk - between two traditional gendered restrooms there is a single all-gender "family" restroom.
comment: Don't need to be a hotel guest. Can park at check-in and just walk in.

name: Kohl's
directions: At customer service
comment: No need to buy anything

name: Panera in Dukes Dining
directions: Two gender neutral restrooms in Panera, first floor of Dukes Dining

name: Starbucks
directions: When you walk into the main front door the restrooms are directly to your right. 2 single stall gender neutral locking bathrooms.
comment: This location is also really good for studying and doing work, even if you don't buy anything.

name: Dark Matter Factory
directions:
Office hours M-F 10am to 5pm
Ring the doorbell.

name: Banheiros do Centro de Artes e Comunicação da Universidade Federal de Pernambuco
street: Avenida da Arquitetura, s/n, Campus Universitário
directions: Tem banheiros em todos os andares, é fácil de achá-los porque eles ficam próximos às escadas no hall de entrada.
comment: Você não precisa estudar no centro para usar o banheiro. Eles são separados por gênero e a política do centro é que cada pessoa pode utilizar o banheiro no qual se sente mais confortável.

name: Dona Vitamina
directions: Bem no fundo do restaurante

name: Carter
comment: 2 separate "unisex" single stalls

name: eyedrum
directions: straight back from door
comment: art venue

name: Minnesota Marine and Art Museum
directions: You need to pay to enter the museum ($10, June 2023)
comment: It's not right on the front, but but near the middle of the small museum. There are 2 single stall restrooms.

name: Joe Jr
directions: Directly in the back, through the orange door
comment: Very tiny bathroom, definitely not accessible. Bathroom is only for paying customers

name: Safeway Grocery
directions: Once you get in the lobby and  on your left. You’ll have to ask someone present for a key.
comment: Paying customers usually, but the guard on weekends will let you in without questioning you.

name: Prédio Administrativo IFSC - Banheiro Acessível
street: Prédio Administrativo I.F.S.C - R. Miguel Petroni, 116-144, Jardim Bandeirantes
directions: Passar pelas catracas na secretaria. Por trás da estrutura vermelha, na frente da sala dos sofás pretos.
comment: Precisa ter qualquer cartão de estudante da USP, não apenas do IFSC. Aberto 24 horas. Há secretária que também pode te deixar passar.

name: Indianapolis Public Library - West Perry Branch
directions: Once you enter, just head left towards the check-out station, there's a hallway with two gendered bathrooms and one unisex.

name: Bento Kitchen Cravings
directions: When you face the cashier, it will be right behind you
comment: Clean, very spacious, gender neutral bathroom

name: Race street cafe
directions: Basement
comment: Great food and service too

name: Walmart
directions: Back of store near electronics
comment: Labeled as mother's room

name: Fellbites
directions: Opposite the entrance slightly to the left there is a door which leads to a room that has 3 stalls in.
comment: The stalls are technically gendered (1 ladies, 1 gents, and 1 disabled) but they're all next to each other in one room so it would literally not matter which one you used.

name: Angell Hall
directions: 5th floor of Angell, near the astronomy classrooms

name: Red ginger Japan steak and sushi
directions: Straight back from the hostess stand.
comment: Stalls are fully walled in and the door has no gaps in it

name: Dave's Hot Chicken
directions: Bathrooms are in hall to the right of registers
comment: Code as of June 24, 2023 is 123456

name: The Broken Axe
directions: Past the bar to the right, two single toilets, one with a urinal, one without.
comment: Owners are straight, but allies, and don't stand for nastiness.

name: 3925 S Rochester Rd, Royal Oak, MI 48073, USA
directions: Up the stairs to the left
comment: Tell the front desk that you are there for the bathroom (say that you know Tom or Kyu[Q])

name: Community Homes, Inc.
directions: Up stairs on left
comment: Tell desk you are there for the restroom (tell them you know Tom or Kyu [Q])

name: Lucky Loggers Landing
directions: Front of restaurant to the left as you walk in

name: Rio Salado Northern
directions: second floor down the little nook where the empty windowed room is

name: Fyrens library
directions: There are restrooms both up and downstairs. The ones downstairs are in between the library and cafe. The ones upstairs are sometimes blocked off but are up the stairs/elevator and away from the seating area.
comment: There is one wheelchair accessible restroom downstairs and that’s also where the changing table is. The library puts out lgbt book recommendations in the entry way occasionally year round and i feel pretty safe there as a trans masculine person.

name: Heine Brothers
directions: Back of the shop on the right side.
comment: All gender single use restrooms.

name: Franklin Memorial Hospital
directions: As you walk up the hall on your way to everything except day surgery, you go right by two unisex bathrooms.

name: Cat Cafe on Whyte
directions: In the front area of the cat room, to the left.
comment: Must purchase admission ($20) into the cat room

name: Cahoon Museum of Art
directions: Lower level

name: Brewer Oil Company
directions: Two gender neutral restrooms available. They lock when you shut the door. Inside straight back.

name: Eagles Beachwear
directions: Go to the leftmost back corner of the store where the pool floaties and toys are. You will find a wooden door and a sign that says: "customer restroom. Please keep neat."

name: Subway
comment: You have to be a paying customer and there is a code

name: Turner Hall
directions: Second floor, west side of building. Closer to the north end of the hall.

name: Edo Japan
directions: Past the counter to the right

name: Tupelo Honey Southern Kitchen
comment: Have to be a customer

name: The Crack Fox
directions: In the back to the right.
comment: Staff is very accepting. 2 single stalls. Restroom signs say "Whatever...Just wash your hands" and have a funny pictogram of a male-presenting and female-presenting person, a space alien, and a bear :)

name: Planet fitness
directions: Go through the locker room and the bathroom and showers are in the back
comment: As a trans woman I have felt safe using there locker room/bathroom

name: Smoothie King
directions: The other end of the store as you walk in. Both restrooms are neutral.
comment: You must ask for a key in order to use them.

name: Sam's Club
directions: Go to the food court, then head to the aisles with razors, medicines, etc, and take a right. The family restroom is in between the two gendered sections.
comment: Just like any other Sam's Club, it requires a subscription in order to get in

name: Dollar Tree
directions: Head to the left side of the store, and go through the left most aisle. The bathroom should be near the frozen section.

name: Goodwill
directions: Head to the section with the DVDs and you will see a little hallways with two doors: one an office, the other a restroom

name: KendalWall, Lakeland climbing centre
directions: Stay on first floor. Through the door, past the cafe and take a left, go along to the bottom of the corridor and it’s on the left.

name: Milkweed
directions: in the back of the coffee shop

name: Beach Life Sweets OKI
directions: In the entrance, keep going straight parallel to the counter until you see it.
comment: May not be the cleanest.
